player.seasonOutlook: Duggan was selected in the seventh round of April's draft. Size (6-foot-1, 207 lbs.) and arm strength are concerns and while he made a bit of a leap in 2022, Duggan's passing efficiency leaves a lot to be desired (career 60% completion rate, 14.4% off-target rate). He didn't show well athletically at the combine, but could add value with his legs in the pros. He totaled a 395-2,510-28 rushing line in 47 games at TCU. Duggan will battle for a backup gig behind Justin Herbert.

DuBose was selected in the seventh round of April's draft. The Charlotte product appeared in only 24 collegiate games (only one WR in this year's rookie class played in fewer), but he was busy when active, handling a 28% target share (fourth-highest). In fact, his 2021 and 2022 usage and production were extremely consistent, as he went from a 62-892-6 receiving line (28% share) in 12 games to a 64-792-9 line (28% share) in 12 games. DuBose is raw and not super quick or fast, but he has good size (6-foot-2, 201 pounds) and is joining a WR-needy Packers roster. He's a long shot for short-term value, but monitor his progression this summer.
